##Local Political Representation in England Datasets 050918

The datasets are an up date of Open Data Manchester's DEPvsREP dataset created on the 24th April 2018 prior to the local elections in England in May 2018.

The dataset was split into three datasets and expanded to include [Electoral Commission political party identity codes](http://search.electoralcommission.org.uk)

The data was collated by Pamilla Kang using python scraping scripts [Github repository](https://github.com/pkkang/Deprivation-in-England) and manually.

READ ME AND LICENCE

This dataset matches council ward representation with IMD2015. This data is created from the Ministry of Housing, Communities & Local Government English Indices of Deprivation 2015 - Index of Multiple Deprivation December 2015 Lookup in England found here https://data.gov.uk/dataset/index-of-multiple-deprivation-december-2015-lookup-in-england3
and the Office for National Statistics - LSOA 2011 to Ward to Local Authority District 2016 Lookup found here http://geoportal.statistics.gov.uk/datasets/output-area-to-ward-to-local-authority-district-december-2016-lookup-in-england-and-wales this data was then manually keyed from the councillor information from the 353 local authorities in England.

LSOA11CD - Unique LSOA identifier
LSOA11NM - Name of Local Authority in which the LSOA is situated
WD16CD - Unique ward identifier
WD16NM - Name of ward
LAD16CD - Local Authority District identifier
LAD16NM - Local Authority District Name
FID - Unique ID
IMD15 - Indices of Multiple Deprivation 2015 ranking
COUNC1 - Elected councillor 1
COUNC2 - Elected councillor 2
COUNC3 - Elected councillor 3
REPR - Balance of representation for ward
URL - Location of councillor information

COUNCILLOR POLITICAL AFFILIATION CODING
C = Conservative - Including Independent Conservatives and Conservative and Unionist
L = Labour - Including Independent Labour and Labour and Cooperative
LD = Liberal Democrat - Including Liberal Party
UKIP = United Kingdom Independence Party
G = Green
O = Other - Independents, Residents groups and other political affiliations
NOR = No dominant representation
V = Vacant seat

Due to the large numbers of councillors in the England representation changes over time and can only be considered correct as of 10th April 2018
Although the data has been checked there maybe manual keying errors in this dataset - please let us know if you find an error or have any questions hello@opendatamanchester.org.uk

